TASK: ENHANCE PROTOCOL TIMELINE UX, PERFORMANCE, AND CLINICAL FUNCTIONALITY

OBJECTIVE:

Improve the protocol timeline visualization to:

- reduce visual density
- enable interactive phase navigation
- improve performance
- support clinical workflows
- enable mobile usability

------------------------------------------------

PHASE 1 — RESTRUCTURE TIMELINE HEADER

Split header information into:

PRIMARY HEADER:

Protocol Name  
Approval Status  
Total Duration  
Number of Phases  
Number of Compounds  

SECONDARY METRICS:

Estimated Cost  
Intensity  
Frequency  

Reduce visual clutter.

------------------------------------------------

PHASE 2 — ENABLE INTERACTIVE PHASES

Make each phase clickable.

On click:

Display Phase Detail Panel.

Panel must include:

Compound name  
Dose  
Frequency  
Phase duration  

------------------------------------------------

PHASE 3 — ADD COMPOUND TOGGLE FILTER

Create compound chips above the timeline.

Example:

[Tirzepatide]  
[MOTS-c]  
[AOD-9604]

Allow:

Toggle visibility on/off.

This improves readability and performance.

------------------------------------------------

PHASE 4 — ADD CLINICAL EVENT MARKERS

Allow optional markers:

Blood tests  
Reviews  
Milestones  

Display as:

Icon markers on timeline.

------------------------------------------------

PHASE 5 — MOBILE ADAPTATION

Implement:

Horizontal scroll timeline.

OR:

Vertical phase cards mode.

Never compress the chart.

Maintain readability.

------------------------------------------------

PHASE 6 — PERFORMANCE OPTIMIZATION

Memoize timeline data.

Use:

useMemo()

Avoid recalculating on every render.

If timeline exceeds:

24 weeks

Implement virtualization.

------------------------------------------------

PHASE 7 — ADD EXPORT CAPABILITIES

Allow:

Export timeline as:

PNG  
PDF  
CSV  

------------------------------------------------

PHASE 8 — ADD COST BREAKDOWN PANEL

Allow clicking cost block.

Show:

Cost per compound  
Cost per phase  
Cost per week  

------------------------------------------------

SUCCESS CRITERIA:

Timeline becomes:

- interactive
- readable
- clinically useful
- mobile-friendly
- scalable
- exportable